If you are looking for an awesome sushi place then this is the place to be! When we sat down they already gave us on the house edamame which was awesome to begin the experience with. We'll be definitely coming back here very soon and, probably, very often.
100% recommended!

Delicious sushi restaurant with great rolls and lunch specials! Location is newly opened, but the 12th location for this chain. Food is more Americanized than traditional Japanese, but delicious if that's what you're looking for! Even basic rolls have good portions of fish, and rolls are good prices. Basic and special rolls all come with 8 pieces. We had their candy cane, earthquake, Alaska, and spicy salmon rolls. Out of those, earthquake was the favorite. Definitely try their house sauce on the rolls as well!!

We had a great time here, sushi was fresh and tasted good. They gave us some complementary sides just for being guests. Loved this place and definitely recommend to anyone looking for a sushi place to try out.

Very nice atmosphere and great quality food. Everything seemed very fresh and they had  very good service. I wasn't a fan of a few items we got, but I believe that was more just my taste and not anything bad to say about them.

I have been to this place total of 2 times now, both lunch and dinner, and the experience has been pleasant! Their specialty is sushi rolls so for the people who like sushi rice(like my wife) this place is great! One difference in the rolls this place offers I personally really enjoy is the rolls are actually slightly warm, it gives a better mouth feel than the typical cold rolls you get elsewhere(disclaimer: I have not ordered rolls with raw fish so i dont know if those are warm as well) The environment  is clean and cozy, its another reason why my wife nags me to come back again and again lol

This was my first order from YamaChen. I was pleased that they combined a couple of the orders of sushi to conserve the waste of take away containers, and that the containers are recyclable. The sushi was fresh and tasty. The restaurant was clean and not crowded. The service, though I said previously was take away, was prompt. I placed my order online, and received a text as soon as it was ready, and it was ready before the estimated time. Very nice. I will be returning as often as my cravings call me. This will be my new go to place for sushi. üç£

I don't do sushi, but I like Japanese, so this is a review of some non-sushi items.

The gyoza were okay, but deep-fried instead of pan-fried, so it's a bit like having those frozen microwavable things from the grocery store. Hot and crispy, but all you taste is the shell.

The chicken teriyaki was not good. It has the basics you'd expect, chicken breast in a sweet brown sauce. But the vegetables they added seemed odd, at least to American tastebuds. I don't know what's considered 'authentic' for this dish, I just know that cherry tomatoes, cabbage, and edamame beans aren't what anybody else serves, and don't work together.

You get the usual salad, which had peanut dressing. I was okay with that, until I took a bite and realized everything had already been tossed with some sweet oil.

Somehow, even the rice had an issue. They serve it on some big (banana?) leaf, I guess for decoration. But the flavor of the leaf, which is kind of musky, bleeds into the rice. This was a problem with the gyoza too. I assume this is an accident, but it doesn't help.

I'm not normally nitpicky, but it's frustrating that nothing tasted like what I expect or hope for.

On the plus side, the decor is pretty good with lots of dark-stained wood, the service was great, and apparently people like their sushi.

Stopped here on my birthday after googling "seafood near me" while visiting richmond.   I'm from fredericksburg, so I was very excited to indulge in what the capital has to offer. I had seen that the sign read "florida style seafood" .  I wanted a more DMV style seafood establishment, but I was already here.   When I entered, I was promptly greeted.   Due to covid-19, the interior was rather barebones: no seating and a homemade lemonade stand.  I was very excited to be here. Their trays were displayed in a cooler and that gave a very good visual representation of what you got when you paid.  I got chicken tenders, clams, and shrimp , and sides .  My shorty got crabs and shrimp and sides. My card was declined because I forgot to transfer my stock money and the staff were extremely patient and understanding. Food is very overpriced. Though the food  does arrive well seasoned and very hot the seafood, in particular the snow crab legs,  were not fresh.  The meat was dried out in the shell and did not slide freely out when cracked.  Though all of the food is extremely pricey (some meals are $125+) the all you can eat option has increased in price from $39.99 to $49.99 and any food you do not (or cannot) finish is now weighed and charged $30/lb extra.   Of course sharing is not allowed and the owner watches you eat on hidden cameras to make sure that you don't (creepy).  I was very bad and gave my son a few mozzarella sticks and about 8 shrimp.  My husband sent back the cheesecake he ordered because it was flat, very dense, and dried out.  They used a stock photo on the menu that the actual item looked nothing like.  Because of the sharing thing the owner would not remove the dessert from the bill and no one told us this until we questioned it.  The owner wouldn't even come speak to us and it was relayed through the waitresses, one of which was rather snotty when queried.  Though we were completely in the wrong I felt it was handled very badly.  I would have paid for the food I shared but the way it was handled was unprofessional.  I feel like we can't  go back again anytime soon because of this.  I can't comment on how well/unwell their business is doing but in the 2 hours we were there there were only two other customers in the entire restaurant so I don't  really know whether they can afford to alienate customers.

As for the atmosphere,  the decor is better suited for Captain D's than for a restaurant where one dish can cost hundreds of dollars.  There are no fewer than 5 big screen TVs spaced around the restaurant set amidst netting, mermaids, and fake fish.  To cap off the tackiness of the decor there are 3 neon bubble wall panels seperating the bar area from the booth dining area.  The tables are covered in a sheet of brown wrapping paper from a roll.  This is not a place I would want to take a date for a special night out.  I can't quite  figure out whether they are going for a tacky seafood restaurant, a sports bar, or an upclass elegant restaurant (as indicated by the price list and 2 pound leather menus).  Diners beware.

Pros:

Food. The food is good we enjoyed the meals that came out and the chef takes a lot of pride and care with his work.

CONS:

Staff/Training: Our waitress was so incredibly nice. I would consider myself easy to please however. For the menu pricing I am honestly expecting more experience with staff to be frank. I felt like I paid Ruth Cris pricing but had a TGI Friday's level of service. As well the staff could definitely be helped with some paid training learning about whiskey basics. Our staff didn't seem very knowledgeable about whiskeys.

The Drink Menu Tablet: Tons of drinks and I loved that however the tablet system felt clunky and I wouldn't bother if I weren't big on whiskey. I think printed Menus with some staple whiskeys like Buffalo, Blantons, Elijah Craig, Wellet, Willets.. etc. Would be nice and have the tablet system available on request. Also would love to see tasting flights!..

The Food Menu: I saw another review that was spot on. I would love to come here and just drink a couple nice bourbons not on my shelf at home regularly with some light appetizers. However the food is meal centric and I don't necessarily want to spend 50+ on a meal with a couple 20 dollar pours on a week night. I would love to see a more casual gastro bar style menu dips/some fried sharable options.

Hope to see this business thrive going forward!

Some pros would be the decor is on point, and the smell when you walk in is appetizering. The food lacks flavor though. I got the special menu crabcake but it lacks any spice or seasoning. 80% is just plain breading. 15% is grease.

Fish tacos were awesome!!!

My last visit used the drive thru and when I got back home the doubled up on the onion rings and no hush puppies.  Went back up and they appoligized and gave me a coupon for a 16 piece meal. Service was great and staff very friendly.
Nice place to eat at, prices are fair, clean Establishment, fast service

Stopped here in the way home from business meeting. It seemed like everyone behind the counter was preoccupied  Ordered 2 chicken, 1 fish combo. Waited 10 minutes for my food. Got on the road, realized that I got 2 fish. At least it was hot.
Good tasted great. There was only a cook and the manager working. The service was extremely slow.
The food was good and the service was great.
Why is this place even still open. No business, horrible customer service, crappy food. There's a reason they are never busy.
Closed :-(
This place is terrible, rude staff, service is slow,  don't waste your money.
Great food, fresh

Great food. Great atmosphere. My mom and I sat outside. The view and light breeze off the water was wonderful and relaxing. This place was great! Clean, friendly staff, and awesome food! The views on the water were spectacular especially at night!!! The really amazing part is there was a lot of really great food and it was shockingly very reasonable!!! I loved it. I am already making plans to go back ASAP!!! And I'm a very picky eater. The only thing I was a bit upset about is that they did not offer sweetened tea...other than that, it was wonderful all around!!!üåüüåüüåüüåüüåü

1st time there,  my wife's 2nd time there.  Great atmosphere, sitting on the James River. Plenty of seafood, I had the fried shrimp and oyster platter. Very good, just like I like it. My wife had several appetizers, fried oysters, stuffed mushrooms,  and She Crab soup. All was great! We took lots of pictures as the scenery  was awesome,  sun setting,  etc. We will definitely go back, highly recommend!

I had a delivery to make for Becky's Buckroe Florist to the owner's today. The inside is beautiful! I loved all the nautical decor. The views of the James River are awesome! I will definitely be back for dinner.
Great food(as you can see in the photo)and great service by Nicole! Enjoyed having dinner on the James and strolling on the pier afterwards. Nice spot to get away for a couple hours. üôÇ

Always a great experience. Service was a little slow this night but all in all the food was good. We were a large party of 13 people on a Sunday evening after the beach. We love coming here afterwards. Fresh seafood and hot plates!
Service a little shaky at first, but food made up for it. The salmon on greens was delicious! Great View too.
Had salmon stuffed with crab. Great food. There is a wait if you go at dinner or sunset but definitely worth the wait!!
Great soft shell crabs, amazing location and gorgeous views of the beach and water. Definitely  sit outside if possible!

Food was good but service was very very very poorly slow. Waited with one couple in front of us for about 40 minutes. No host. Took another 20 minutes to get our order taken. Then another 40 minute wait for food to come. They was not busy at all.

The service was excellent but the food wasn't good..  they ran out if soup, I got scallops with huge onions on top of huge bed of coleslaw for 24 dollars,  my son's burger was raw.. for 100 dollars meal we won't come back again
I don't eat meat, but do eat Kosher fish. They always accommodate me by preparing grilled salmon over the Zito pasta Alfredo. Absolutely divine. Of course the view is to die for.üíû
Very great authentic fresh seafood. Fantastic experience with very friendly staff.

Been wanting to try this place and finally got to. Burger was good, but the fried shrimp was bland. Even with Old Bay & Cocktail Sauce. 20.00 for shrimp that tastes like it was bought in the frozen section at any store I do not reccomend.

Went today for the 3rd time. The 1st time was just appetizers and they were decent. 2nd time I had the fried platter. It was ok. Nothing to write home about, but today I decided to give it another try. I will not be back.

We got the fried calamari,  crab dip, shrimp salad, crab cake sandwich with fries and fried shrimp and fries. The best thing we ate were the fries. The crabcake was tasteless, the crab dip and calamari was extremely salty. The shrimp was not deveined. My daughter was not pleased about that. The shrimp salad was bland. It was just a bland, boring meal.

Wont go back.
Crab stuffed salmon and baked potato was delicious, customer service was excellent as well.

Slow asked for silverware. My daughter finally went and got it. The service was not the best or the food. But I did not complain because someone took me there for my birthday they was really excited.  And I did not want to make things worse.
Delicious food. Beautiful location. Service was somewhat slow, but like everyplace right now I believe they were short staffed.

Food was awesome and service was great. The reason I give 4 stars is because the crab soup didn't have hardly anything in it. It is a nice spot and would definitely recommend it. Make your crab soup better and I will give 5 stars happily. For being right on the water, it is important that your crab soup beats the competition of places that had better crab soup.
Nothing but awesome!! Clean place, friendly staff, fresh seafood, great selection, right on the James River and...homemade Key Lime Pie!!! Great experience :-D
Having a nice quiet lunch with my Husband next to the River watching the Birds and Ducks..The best lunch ever! Very Romantic! Very nice friendly staff!
Excellent service and the food was amazing...The staff was super friendly and the view is so beautiful.Put this place on your to do list you will not be disappointed
The food and service were fantastic.   My family and I thoroughly enjoyed it.
Good food, great location; the only publicly accessible river front restaurant in Newport News! That's a shame.
Service was trash. The waitress forgot about us. The food was pretty good and the view was amazing. They need new leaders and new servers.

3 stars are for great service. Personally, I wasn't a fan of the food. The spinach dip was great but the fried shrimp in the picture were under seasoned and were not cleaned, they still had the digestive tract in place. Also, they can hardly be described as fried as you can see in the image I posted. Other members of my party noted that their food was not seasoned. Service was excellent and that is what earned 3 stars.

Food was good at a great price. Ordered scallops for $23 and got 8 scallops! And they were good! Perfect place to watch the sunset. Parking is free, but wished they had more parking. Service was okay. Waitress seemed frazzled because the restaurant was busy. She served my salad on a tray that had dirty dishes on it, and also served our drinks on a tray that had dirty dishes on it too. We notified the manager and she brought me a new salad.
Food,drinks and service are great,you will be back..and it's on the james river

My Stepdaughter and my self, meet at the Crab Shack on the James. As always the food was so delights. Had warm crab dip, so good. Then carb cakes,  no shell's it wasn't the taste she had been wanting. I got crab legs cooked perfect. You always know when the Cook know how to cook them. When you opened the the leg meat came out hole. OMG it was all perfect. I know I'll be back
Meh...my fries were cold when they came out, but my friend's fries were hot.

On of the greatest team I've meet during this troublesome time. Very friendly and professional as a matter of fact this was my first time there but, it seems I was with friends I hadn't see for a few days.
Keep up the great service and stay safe.

This restaurant is hit & miss, but usually miss in my experience.  Great location and great atmosphere!  But the food is a roll of the dice.  Some meals in our party(s) were excellent, but others were purely inedible.  If avoiding the sea food, I don't recommend any chicken they prepare (be it a sandwich or whatever).  The service is fine.  It's just the food that motivates this 2-star feedback.

Great food prices and service. If you come when it‚Äôs busy, there‚Äôs always a wait so be patient.
This place is some of the best seafood on Virginia's east coast, great service fast service, beautiful view of the  Hampton Roads
Amazing views and excellent staff

Have always loved the Crab Shack!  The food is spectacular!  However, I have now been sitting with an empty glass for some time now, and our server has walked passed our table at least twice and has not refilled my drink.  This is a deal breaker for me since I do drink a lot...in volume.  In addition,  we were seated right next to another party.  Not 6 feet minimum per the department of health mandates!

Alway good food and great service here and the setting on the river is very relaxing.

Food was excellent, hot and tasty.  Atmosphere was really nice on the water, by the James River bridge entrance. Sunset was beautiful!
20 of us went: we ordered crab dip, calamari,
a variety plate of shrimp, tilapia and crab cake; tuna sandwich; oysters, and about everything on the menu as well as chicken tenders for 8 kids. And the drinks were very "refreshing".
We drove an hour to get there, and I was well worth it. The waitress was amazing, and the food was great. We cleaned our plates and left full and happy.
Food was good.  Outside was pretty hot late in the day.

A wonderful experience yet again!  Server Heather did a wonderful job making me feel welcome and important.  As it looked like she did with other guests!  Food was spot on and very tasty!  Heather made fantastic recommendations!  Place was very clean and all current pandemic rules were being followed.  Will definitely recommend this restaurant!
Tyler is and excellent server!! Food was tasty as usual. None of our party liked the she crab soup, but they were nice enough not to charge us.

Amazing food and lovely staff. They also have some of the cutest kitties that live there as a part of the restaurant! The view is insane as well!
Great service and the food was awesome. Amazing views while you eat

It was absolutely beautiful to eat here when the sun was about to set. This place is right on the water, not to mention the soft shell crab was so delicious. Would definitely recommend people to come here if they're in the area.
Very nice place! Had the crab cake sandwich without bread and she crab soup.  Both were very good.  Nice atmosphere! Great staff! I will be back with family!
As a Marylanders, the she crab soup and crab cakes were under seasoned. Service was good and setting was beautiful.  We are from AZ SO we enjoyed the view.
Delicious food and great outdoor seating.
Great atmosphere. Good food reasonably priced.
5 for ambiance and location, 3 for food unfortunately. The steamed shrimp was the best!
Always a great view and the food was definitely good!
Food good, except she crab would too peppery.  Beautiful view of sunset.  Service a tiny bit slow, but all in all a good experience.  Would return.
Awesome place. Awesome food
Amazing!! Very peaceful &relaxing
Great food and great service!
Food was great and the view awesome!
Great view of the james river. Oyster were nice & plump. Steamed shrimp & calamari were excellent.

I used to love this place because it is right by the river and food was good; however, something has changed and this time the service was horrible, orders were wrong and the quality of the food was bad - my oyster had dirty and the crabs were cold. Not going back ever again.
Place of memories with family and kids had a good dinner shrimp was delicious
Awesome food and service. Beautiful surroundings. My favorites place when I am in Va

Great service! Mediocre food.

Great food. Been there during the Newport News Restaurant Week. It was awesome! The location of the restaurant is just on the James River and has a wonderful view and design. Love!! However, the service wasn‚Äòt too great and borderline rude.
Great atmosphere. No wait. Great food. Great service. Probably my favorite restaurant in the area.

Best crab cake sandwich in Virginia!
One star because of the awesome view.  Service and cleanliness were a miss.  Food is OK.  Now I remember why I don't go there!
Excellent as usual. Service and food outstanding. Hard shells were pricey, but that's why we go there.

Best seafood. Great views.
Snow crab legs were really good, and I received a generous amount for the money. Great place to sit outside and enjoy some fresh seafood.

Nice restaurant, we sat outside: we got there approximately 12:20 today and service was pretty slow, but the volume wasn't high.

The she crab soup is okay, could use more crab meat. The oysters on the half shell are the worst oysters I've had this far... Very bland... No sweetness to them at all or distinguishing flavors.

On the plus side... Their shrimp prawns are great! Highly recommend the shrimp here and that, along with water, will probably be the only things I ever order here again.

Crab bisque or crab soup whatever they want to call it, never tastes good for some reason. Bad texture or fishy aftertaste. The prices are high for what you get. The only plus side to coming here is the views. Oh and the servers are. ...??? MIA... when you need them. Yet there are so many sitting around talking with other tables. Weird.

First time going. Restaurant was clean staff very friendly and attentive to customers. Though we didn't dine outside because of weather the view is nice. Food was very good and reasonably priced. I would go back
Good food, great service, and nice atmosphere. Definitely worth a stop!

I enjoyed both the food and service at the Crab Shack. I've been there several times and each time I've been pleased. The food prices are reasonable and the food is tasty. I definitely would recommend it as a favorite spot of mine. Also, nice scenery!
The people were great the food wasn't.

Great views and right on the water. Had the raw oysters. If ur a fan of oysters do not go here. They are warm and not quality oysters. The day I went they must of had a new oyster worker bc nothing but dirt and shells in the oyster. Ahi tuna sandwich was good. But probably wouldn't ho back unless it was for just drinks.
Absolutely beautiful Sunset
Good waterview, great food and awesome staff.

Me and my family, we used to love this place, the food is awesome and it's inexpensive, until 2 days ago. The server got all our food, except my daughter, they had forgotten it. Anyway, we started eating our food, to find out my husband's fish is raw. It took a while for us to finally find someone to help us, because we did not find our waitress. So, She took my husband food, re cook it, and served it back again just like that, it was very un appetizing, and No apologies. Needless to say, we are not coming back. We always give good tip but that was the first time we gave only $2.

Good views of Hunnington Beach. On our last visit 10/11, the floors and tables were sticky. The food was not worth the price. The shrimp jammers, pictured below, seem liked fried frozen products. The crab meat on our chicken sandwiches was cold and not fresh.

Upon receiving my order I was disappointed to see that I had a plate full of Lettuce under my main course! This was due to the small portion of my actual meal. By their doing so makes it  appears to be more food and decorative. My shrimps were too salty but will say my oysters were good. However overall I was not impressed and will not recommend to others.
Very good food

The 3 stars are for the view and the Jimmy Buffett music. It took too long to seat one person, restaurant wasn't busy. Server was slow, took an order from another party that came in after me before taking mine. The oysters Rockefeller were tasty but too salty and gritty. I'll only come back for the view!

While i have read some reviews that were less than good, i found the food to be very good. The crab stuffed mushrooms were very good and the salmon was excellent.  Service was also good, had to wait a little bit for dinner, but was worth the wait, food arrived at our table hot and cooked perfectly.

Fantastic! At first i did not like the coleslaw but it eventually grew on me. Light on dressing and more vinegar than i like. I would recommend if getting crabcakes get them grilled not friend. The breading soaked up wayyy to much of the flavor of the oil and it really affected the taste. Otherwise great crabcakes, dessert is a must of course! Ooo and 100% try the shrimp jammers. They have plenty of space for seating.
Ok food, service was good.
Oyster platter, talpia fish sandwich better than usual, yea!
Awesome views and delicious food. Friendly cats also.
Beautiful setting. Great food and service.
Stopped in for lunch, the food was amazing.  Friendly staff, amazing views.
I love the outside eating area! Love their blue crab drink too! Great service! The waitress was very friendly and very familiar with the menu. So she was helpful in deciding what to order!

Fun atmosphere with view of the James River either eating inside or out on the screen porch.  Food is delicious and not only seafood but various items on menu to choose from.  Always had good service and pleasant experience....Highly Recommend!!
Everything was amazing and the service was amazing! I will be back soon!

Fantastic food, beautiful view of the water, fishing pier and James River Bridge. Staff is friendly. Our #1 place to take family and friends from out of town who love seafood. Nothing fancy, nor reservations needed. Just a local favorite that says,"this is why we live in Hampton Roads" üòç
The service was amazing, and the food was delicious!!!!  One hundred percent recommend going there!

Ordered the fried shrimp appetizer, oyster Rockefeller, shark shrimp (bang bang knock-off), shack burger, and chicken tenders with fries for the kiddo.    The chicken tenders and fries are the only thing I‚Äôd order again.  Ever eaten something and thought ‚Äúmeh‚Äù?   That is what we experienced with all of our food.   The views of the James and the ambience were great, but due to the mediocrity in flavors we won‚Äôt be back.   There is a nice beach right next door though!!!

Virtually no parking. They should have valet service on weekends to keep open designated parking spaces for customers. Service was terrible and slow. Crab dip had very little or no crab in it. Entree's were very good and cooked nicely. I had crab stuffed flounder and snow crab legs. But once again, crab stuffing had little or no crab in it. Views are beautiful and atmosphere is nice. Such potential here, but we were disappointed.

This is the second time I have eaten here.  The first time we had oyster Rockefeller and she crab soup.  The oysters we're five star but the soup was so thick it was almost like mashed potatoes.

This time I had the oysters Rockefeller and the fish and chips special.  Once again the oysters we're perfect.  The fish breading was soggy as we're the fries.  Both were warm and not hot....like it sat under a heating lamp.

The atmosphere is nice. Every seat has a water view.  The staff was friendly as well.
Love,  Love this place,  the food,  staff is great and the view beautiful

We've been here for lunch several times. The food is always good. Today they had cod fish and chips (they don't always have cod) as a special. It was great! I got the coleslaw instead of fries. It was very fresh and yummy. We had the crab dip today. It was delicious! Lots of crab, very cheesy and served with plenty of toasted French bread. We absolutely will eat here again.
Good food and service fair price
Pretty good, the fish didn't taste fresh, the rest was good
Good food. Great atmosphere...

The Crab Shack was amazing.  It made for a nice afternoon stop. It was a wonderful surprise and the food was as amazing as the view was.  Our waitress, Amanda was awesome and added so much to our day.
Great drinks, beautiful view and fantastic food at an affordable price.

We were there yesterday afternoon after 2 before the dinner hours for most restaurants.
Not even the drank was good, maybe the machines need servicing for the correct syrup to carbonation ration. Food was not good, they didn't even give me the correct items, waitress was nice, will never return, we didn't eat the food it was so bad and took 40 minutes to prepare,  not worth the wait. We ate inside but flies were everywhere. They must have soaked shrimp, fish and crab in something that taste like ammonia to have a longer expiration date on their seafood but all the food taste like that substance, sending
Food  back makes no difference, it all has the same taste. Don't understand why they are still open with food that bad, now I understand why there were so many empty seats/tables, seemed to be more people at the bar than dinner tables....
Really good food and great views

Wonderful atmosphere and service, I always go with the blackened tuna and as always it did not disappoint, seasoned and thick, cooked Medium well, that's how I always get it and this one here was spot on, kudos to the chef, Nice little bar with views of the James River Bridge, as with tradition we always walk the pier after our meal, rain or shine, so dress accordingly if you so desire to take the walk, enjoy.
Great seafood
It was fine. Very typical of most of the seafood places around here. Great location though!

Ordered a few appetizers,
The stuffed mushrooms were still raw and cold on the inside and they were completely waterlogged. The Shea crab soup smelled and tasted awfully similar to cream of mushroom with spices and crab meat in it. That came out lukewarm at best. The crab meat tasted previously frozen, which I do not mind but it tasted freezer burnt. If it was considered not Shea crab, it would be a good soup. The only good thing I tried was the fried shrimp with jalapeno, those were good.

If you're looking for Shea crab soup, not the best place for me but to each their own.  It is hand made there which I discovered when I bit into a raw clump of the roux they used to thicken the soup.

Also, I personally think the lettuce on the plates to hold the appetizers isn't very aesthetic.

One of the few places to go for fresh, local seafood in an area that paradoxically is surrounded on all sides by water. But you don't come here for the food -- although it's good; or the prices, which are on the steep side; or the service, which is generally mediocre. You come here for the view. Sit out on the covered porch and watch the sun set over the James River. Say it with me. Aaaah.
Service was terrible.
We really enjoyed it here.  Nice bartender, wonderful view, great fried fish.
Beautiful location.  Delicious and properly cooked food.  The four of us ordered a wide assortment of menu items, and we enjoyed all of them.  Our server was friendly and knowledgeable, too.
We sat on the deck. It was super hot but if the food had been good it wouldn't have mattered. Super nice waitress but the food was not good.
It's just a Beautiful  peaceful  nicely decorated  place!! & the water is a Plus!! The food is good!!
Dining here makes me feel like I am on vacation. Fresh seafood, gorgeous sunsets, and an relaxed vibe! A WIN every time!
The she crab soup was aweful. Literally tasted like a cream sauce, no crab. Very odd. Fish was overcooked, batter was very dark. Nice view!
Awesome food and  atmosphere. And a great view of the river.

The atmosphere was good, food was alright was expecting better quality for the price. Had the fried shrimp with fries and Cole slaw  my daughter had the same two sodas and a crab cake. Almost 62 dollars, not including the tip. A bit pricey, I won't be going back any time soon.
Awesome food. Good views. Friendly staff. Prices reasonable. A must visit place
Crab shack is a good seafood place and you really can't beat the view. Drink specials are decent and the price is reasonable.

We've been huge fans of "The Shack" for years! After over 14 years of being a regular customer I can say they're a great family run restaurant with views that can't be beat! Check out the Shack Chicken or Shack Burger, and they always have a few decent craft beers.
Just Beautiful place to eat. View of the ocean and wonderful customer service.  Food is awesome and prices is reasonable. You will love it

Overpriced for actual food quality and ambience. Blue crabs are kind of small. I expect better from a non chain restaurant. There are more upscale places for a close price and better places that are cheaper. Many much better options in Virginia Beach. Good location for the downtown folks.

My wife and I had lunch here while spending the weekend in Newport News. Food was great and so was the service. My waitress was new but she did a awesome job. The waitress told me to try the flounder sandwich meal and it was beyond what I was expecting. Everything was fresh to the point my wife was eating off my plate. I would definitely visit again on my next trip to Newport News.
Great server but food was okay. Would have liked to see a PO boy on the menu. Have to try the coleslaw. Different but very delicious.
Been going here since they 1st opened( oh no....I am showing my age,lol). The Food and Service is always good.
Food is awesome, everyone was very friendly and interacted with customers.
Great prices, awesome food, and a great setup and atmosphere!
Perfect views of the sunset. Crab cake sandwich was tasty. Great beer. Server was a little weak. Could have sold us desert. But didn't try to hard. Friendly though.

The server was terrible. She didn't refill our drinks not once. Didn't bring our sauces like cocktail and tartar sauce hot sauce. We had to ask the greeter. I  asked for my fried seafood platter to be fried extra crispy and it wasn't. My fries and wifey baked potato was cold I didn't want to ask for more hot food scarred that it wouldn't be healthy for us. I won't be coming back. My experience was very small, but very bad. A friend recommended the Crab Shack and raved, saying they had a great meal and a wonderful time but unfortunately this was not my experience. I popped in for an app and a drink at about 3:30pm during the week (not prime time). The restaurant is **right** on the river at the foot of the Rt 17 James River bridge and had ample seating right on the water. The hostess was a sweet teenage girl with braces, and although it had kind of a touristy
vibe, it was very clean and gave a good first impression. I sat outside next to the water and asked if there were any happy hour specials. I was advised that happy hour is only at the bar, but no food specials for offered, but there were a few drink specials, so I decided to move inside to see what was on offer and it all went downhill from there.

The woman behind the bar was extremely rude and had a rough appearance and manner. Very brusque, didn't make eye contact, and just wanted to know "what do you want" without any explanation of choices. I like wine, but was disappointed in the wine by the glass options so I got a mixed drink ($8) which was fairly thrown at me in a rocks glass full of ice. If it was an 8oz glass there was possibly 2oz of drink in it. I'm not saying I was looking to get drunk at 3:30 in the afternoon, but I didn't feel like it was $8 worth of drink and the delivery left a lot to be desired.

Oysters Rockefeller arrived promptly,(5 for $9) but as soon as they came out I knew it was not something that anyone could or would eat. The oysters themselves were fresh  but the topping consisted of thick, brown, burned greasy spinach that had obviously been stewing in bacon grease and / or possibly fried on a dirty griddle... I don't know how many days old it was  but it was utter sludge and completely inedible. I asked for the check because I wasn't worth it to have a confrontation with the bartender. I think I read that situation pretty clearly because she didn't blink when she picked up the full plate of oysters from the bar in front of me. As she shovelled it into the trash without asking what was wrong, I asked, do they always come out like that? And she said yes. So if that's the case that's the last $20 they'll ever get out of me.

On the ride home I thought long and hard about the last time I was treated so poorly or served something so disgusting, but this was a new low. I'm over it now, but I was mad all the way home. I would never go back or recommend it to anyone else. If they can't even get a drink and appetizer right I'm sure as heck not going to gamble $50pp for dinner.

It also has a beautiful location right on the James River, which at sunset makes for a wonderful setting! Great little hole in the wall seafood Restaurant. It is a bit tricky to find, but when you find it you will never forget how to get back. It is located right before (or after) the Jame River Bridge that connects Hampton and Smithfield. The restaurant catches all of their seafood daily so the menu is subject to change based on availability. The Crab Shack is literally connected to the JRB fishing pier and you can see people fishing from where you are enjoying your food/meal. The restaurant also overlooks the Elizabeth RIver and the Hampton beach which can be quite calming.

SInce the restaurant shares a parking lot with the fishing pier, the parking lot is a bit confusing on who is a restaurant customer and a person who is fishing. Parking lot can be cleaner but more than likely the view of the water will distract any customer.

The staff is friendly and effective. The waitresses are knowledgeable and fun to chat with when you do not know what to order. Service is substantially fast considering the volume of customers they have seated at any given time. There is a small bar customers can sit at though it is a bit hidden. Pricing is a little steep. I decided I wanted chicken.  But I had ordered so much from KFC lately I decided I needed a change.  And I have heard good things about Popeyes from friends before.  So, I decided, why not order from them?
So I went online and found out I could order from many delivery services.  One was Doordash and one was Grubhub.  As I trust Grubhub a little more I ordered from them.  But I noticed that Doordash's delivery fee was smaller and while they still added to the menu prices, like 30 or 40 cents per items, it wasn't that pricey.  As I wasn't ordering a lot, in hindsight, ordering from Doordash MIGHT have been a better idea.  But let's move on with the review on POPEYES ordered via Grubhub.
I ordered a 3 piece Chicken Dinner (Spicy) with Red Beans and Rice, a Biscuit, and a large Diet Coke.
It got to me on time, after they did the change-the-ETA thing, and the driver was not only very polite but warned me about the lid on the drink.  It was cracked in two places and he suggested that Popeyes was using cheap plastic in their lids.  I thanked him for the warning.
The Diet Coke was cold, the somewhat small Biscuit was salty as heck, the Chicken Dinner (a leg, a thigh, and a wing) was meant to be spicy but I only detected spice on the thigh.  It was the GOOD level of spice - just adding enough heat without covering the taste - but it was only added to one piece.  And the Red Bean and Rice seemed to be mostly red sauce with some rice and, to be honest, invisible beans.  Because I don't think I found any.  Or I failed to taste them.  I even took a photo and can't tell if it had beans or not.  It felt like I was eating watered down soup.
Over all, for what I got, for how disappointing it was, and for what it cost I should have gone with KFC and ended up with a much better meal.
Update - Ordered via Grubhub because there was a deal.  Why else would I order from them?  And they got the order right.  Kind of?  The Spicy Chicken Sandwich was good.  The Cajun Fries and Coleslaw was good.  The Chicken Tenders were...sad and the Biscuit was salty.  But the Diet Coke was cold and at least they know what Sweet Tea is. Unlike McD's which seems to think sweet tea is weak soda. But Popeyes forgot all the sauces I asked for.  So maybe add a star to make the total three?  Still not impressed and wonder how this location is still in business.

So came to Red Lobster looking for a decent Friday night meal with the family.  Unfortunately, the overall experience was less than enjoyable.  Shalanta T was our server.  At first it seemed like it was going to be the meal we expected.  I was wrong. When the salads came out we had no rolls yet.  Ok no big deal baking might be a hair behind.  Then here comes the meal right after the rolls finally made it.  We spend most of our time passing plates around.  Ok.  Fine I will wait on myself. Just figured she had lost her 25% at that time.  So as we eat crab legs, we have been given no place to put the shells.  Time to get resourceful.  We fashon the roll basket into a catch all by adding napkins to the bottom. This was hardly enough for two orders of crab legs.  So let's talk about the meal.  Crab was extremely soggy from sitting down in the water. Some parts were cold. So got about half the flavor at that point and our hands were soaked the whole time.  Thank God for the corn.  It was spot on.  So we continue to eat and here comes Shalanta.  Slaps the bill down and says she will take it when we are ready.  No-do you need anything else, no-want dessert...just here and gone.  So I continue eating.  Approximately 8 min later here she comes. "I'll just go ahead and take that from you". Now mind you my hands look like I just birthed a whale.  I told her I hadn't even looked at it yet.  I got an "oh.  I guess when your ready.  Can I take your plates?".  At this point she just stands there with her hands outstretched.  She expects my family to hand her plates she can clearly reach.  I finally had enough.  I stood up and went to the men's room to wash up.  Mind you I went that whole meal with one cloth napkin.  No wet towelettes, no paper napkins, nothing.  So I figured I'd get washed up and find a manager.  Let them know what was going on.  After walking down the hall and back with no manager anywhere, I figured they have lost the opportunity to make it right.  I am tired of waiting on myself and I was leaving.  I gave them a shot.  Since no one was there to fix it.  They get this review.  Sad really.  Dine there with caution.

This was my first visit here and I have mixed feelings. We came for lunch and we were the first ones there. The waitress was prompt and friendly and it didn't take very long for a food to get there. But as the restaurant fillefd the service slowed down and I saw two couples leave without being served. I ordered fish tacos and french fries. The fish tacos were okay although the fish was a little overdone and the cheese have been added and was melted already. I prefer to be able to add cheese lettuce and tomato separately after it's served. They also didn't have the option of fried fish, only broiled or blackened. While the french fries were very good there weren't many. Most restaurants serve you more fries and you can eat. My friend ordered the shrimp and chicken and she said it was very good. I tried one of her hush puppies and they are gold standard for me in a restaurant. The ones here were not that good. The other issue was the decor which was minimal at best. And the booth seats were much too low and not geared towards being able to comfortably reach your food. Overall I'm not sure I will be coming back.

Always great crabs, but their service has gotten very slow and it wasn't even that busy the day we visited. Prices seem to be going up every visit, too! If you're going to raise prices, at least ensure service is above par!
Best place for crabs around. Great food and service.
The maryland blue crabs are fantastic. The crab cakes are also a favorite. Good food all around -- highly recommend.
Best crab cakes in the DC Area. Full Stop. Don't bother ordering crabs. Just enjoy the best the Chesapeake Bay has to offer with a side of Cole Slaw.
Always HOT, always FRESH, Always AMAZING. BEST CRABS AROUND. Super consistant
Very good food.  Lobster roll was good although not great.  Everything crab related we got was very good.  Loved the crab dip and mini crab balls.

Wow, factory farmed seafood at fresh caught prices. This place was depressing to endure. The food was basic at best. The utensils and building were falling apart and the waiter was non attentive. I will not return to this establishment. I am just confused as to how they still in business??

Where do I start....smh....went here for Anniversary Dinner...wanted to get the "Crabfeast" option but was told that the entire dinner party has to order it!! I am an avid crab eater and this is the 1st & ONLY place I've been to that does this! Mind you my hubby don't eat crabs and I had 2 kids with me also! Why would we pay $220 for 1 PERSON to eat at the most 15 small crabs!!
So they ordered food which was overpriced and bland...I ended up ordering half doz(exactly 6) medium crabs (smalls) which 2 were watery&dead and they were $37!!! Smh...started to rain and they told you that you had to go! Never bought anyone bags but made sure the bills came and rudely told people to clear the restaurant and it was pouring down raining lightning and thundering!! The only good thing was the crab hushpuppy (pictured) drinks were terrible stick with the beer..

Crabs were very good and we did not have to go all the way to Maryland to get some, which was great. Crab dip was also incredible and had huge chunks of crab in it. Would recommend to people who don't want to make a trek to the Maryland shores!
Great food at a great price! I will definitely go again and highly recommend.
Great outdoor seating.

Freshest hottest seafood in the area... handsdown!! Service was excellent, great prices!  Tv' s with all the sports playing all around us but comfortable enough for us to have great conversation with each other and some other patrons that are frequent flyersüòä We had a great time and look forward to coming back a lotüòä
Great crabs. More expensive than captain pells but real estate etc. Had a great time and the service was outstanding.

Went to Quarterdeck for lunch and enjoyed the atmosphere and the pleasant wait staff. Ordered the fried oysters that were lightly breaded, flavorful, but way overcooked - dry. The spiced shrimp (served warm) were awesome! I will definitely go back.
I think best of best place. The crab was very fresh and full inside. I think I don't have to find another one to eat crabs anymore.
It's where we go when we do not want to boil or own crab. Great hidden place.
Staff is friendly and upfront about food times especially when ordering crabs. Decent beer selection. Onion rings are good!
Good food. Atmosphere not so great

This place is a hidden gem. I've lived near by but have never had the chance to go there. The food was great, the staff was attentive and nice. Plus it has a pretty sweet bar that is open late. Will definitely head back.

The drinks were watered down.  It was 95% mostly mixer.  The food was very bland.  Mac and cheese had no salt or pepper.Crab dip was more like a quiche. It did have crab in it.  Bland taste.  You have to doctor up your food there.  The crab cakes were good. Ceasar  salad was kid size. There was half of a saucer of lettuce. It took 50 minutes for the crabs to come to the table.  The worst part was the service. Very slow. I had to keep asking for things.  It took 15 minutes for a pitcher of water to be refilled.
Great crabs and fish and chips. They take reservations. I wish I would've known that before going. I highly recommend making a reservation. The food was with the wait.

One of Arlington's best kept secrets. The seafood will knock your socks off. Probably a good idea to make reservations but if you're a little patient and a lot lucky you can be seated. Highly recommend.
Good food!!!!! A lil pricey but worth it.

Really liked it. crabs were great, sides were okay, and shrimp and drinks were good. however, make reservations wayyyyy in advance (like weeks) if you're going on the weekend and I would imagine happy hour times. our group didn't know that and had to wait a while for seating (aka 30-45 mins). will definitely be back for more crabs.

I've been craving seafood like crazy these last few days and I had to get some crab legs! This is my second time at Quarterdeck and I was hoping that it wouldn't disappoint.

Me and a friend arrived at 6pm on a Saturday. The last time I visited, i came on a whim and the wait wasnt too bad, so i wasn't overly concerned about this trip.

We waited to be seating in a line outside of the patio area. I was dissatisfied that no one welcomed us until about 15mins of standing. I will give it to the staff that it appeared really busy and since I was with a friend we just chatted since we weren't in a rush.

The biggest room for improvement would DEFINITELY be the reservation/seating system. It appears that reservations(no matter what the time) trump's a walk-in customer. Everyone was directed to the line whether you have a reservation or not, but then staff ask everyone in-line if anyone had a reservation, and anyone who did were fast passed through the line. For example, we had a couple join the line who had a 630 reservation(they were early for the reservation, but we had been there in line for 15mins before they showed up and they were seated before us). It seemed disorganized and could be off putting for customers. If you prefer reservations, maybe that should be stated.

The most important thing for me was that the craving for crab legs was satisfied, I chose green beans and fries and the fries were mushy, but everything else was great.

Quarterdeck it will be my go to local seafood spot. But I clearly will have to make reservations so that I can be acknowledged in a better manner upon arrival.

The king crab legs were old -meaning they were dried out on the ends. The MD crab soup was on the tasteless side. I added some tobasco sauce, but it didn't help. My tenderloin steak (filet mignon) was tender and prepared as I ordered (medium-rare). There was just not enough mushroom sauce. The fried oysters appetizer was excellent. Service was friendly and infrequent -i got up several times for napkins, steak sauce, and to order.
Awesome crabs! Great service. Highly recommended, we'll be back!
Great food and service!! 1st visit. Will not be my last!
Great place! A bit too expencive but very good. It is always crowded though. And the bathroom lines are long and not easy accessable. The wait is also long sometimes.
This is the place for crabs. Nothing fancy. Just be prepared for the best crab experience in your life.
My favorite place in the world üåé.

Been going here about 35 years.  Now mainly a crab house, the crabs are wonderful and good sized, tho a little pricey, as is the beer.  Service is superb and friendly.  Not a fancy place, but we love it.  Crabs available year round.

The staff is completely unorganized and serve people at random instead of in any kind of working order. I think they just get so swamped that they done care but they kept serving people who came in after us before they would serve us. We waited over an hour to get seated then sat there for an hour uncomfortably and left hungry.  We wasted our Saturday here and will never be back. Had high Hope's as we love seafood but left disappointed.
Food is delicious. Staff is friendly.  Salmon could had used a lil more season but it was good all the same.  Will be back before the end of summer.

Almost looks like a dump from the outside, inside is cramped and crowded but food is Great. Enough said.

Very disappointed by the overall meal.  My first time eating here and will not be going back.  Our server was great.  Figure out a better seating system when folks show up for lunch.
Best Maryland crabs in town!! Fresh & cooked to order. Try the crab dip & crab hush puppies...can't go wrong, it's all delicious!! This place is a NOVA gem.

We arrived here after a quick Google search. What a find! We were seated right away without reservations. Who knew they were needed. Now we all know. Needless to say, it's worth it. The crab cakes are a MUST. No fillers, all crab. Skip the coleslaw though. Snow crab legs are another must try. Next time I visit I'm going for the all you can eat crabs.
Great food and service in a quaint little restaurant.
Amazing crab dip. It was the only thing I ordered and , it was just amazing!!!!
Reminds me of a seafood joint at home that sits right on the mouth of the bayou. And that's a really good thing.

This is a staple in the residential area south of route 50. They offer outdoor seating and are dog friendly. One of the few places in Arlington where the happy hour beer is $3!!! That's for domestic beers, they do offer a wide array of craft beer too. Crab dip is also very good, they can substitute the bread for extra veggies.
It wasn't that busy but our waiter forgot about us several times , but the food was great so I will go back .

I always enjoy myself when we stuff ourselves on crabs and drinks here at the Quarterdeck.  Crabs have always been great and perfectly seasoned.  This place is a local staple or institution for grabbing crabs.

This place is a combination of pub and restaurant, excelling at both!  A neighborhood favorite, you can catch locals taking in the Nationals, Redskins and other hometown favorite teams, cheering their teams to victory.  While locals come here regularly, all are welcome as it is also a major point of curiosity for out-of-towners who are looking for a bite to eat. Far from standard pub food, amazing crab dip, fresh salads, and clam chowders are among the delicious fare they offer.  I must add that although they offer many food options including burgers, fries and the like, they are renowned for their seafood.  They offer 3 kinds of crab legs as well as a blue crab special (at market price).   They have a great bar with friendly bartenders that provide good conversation, service and music.  If you enjoy a quiet setting, you can sit in the dining area where they have a great number of tables, including options to eat outside year round. If you are looking for a great small business with flair, this is the place.  I have a plan to try every dish on the menu as I can hardly make up my mind each time I show up.
Great food but way too small of a location. Also the service is pretty bad in all honesty. The waiters and especially the bartenders could be a lot more courteous.

The employees here are wonderful and the food has always been fantastic UNTIL LAST NIGHT. It was the worst food i have ever had in any restaurant, and I eat out all the time! The pork barbecue tasted like it was days old and warmed in a microwave,  the baked beans were out of a can and warmed up in a microwave,  the asparagus was rock hard, the tea tasted like sugared water, and no paper straws were provided. I will never eat here again and neither will my friends who were with me. I don't know what has happened. Maybe a new cook? Cutting back on quality? Such a shame.
You have to try this local place.  Great local made food.  We liked the Trout,  shrimp,  and crab fluff.  Worh the trip.  Very friendly staff.  Family feeling.

Inexpensive comfort food in a small restaurant setting with lovely seaside decor. The wait staff are helpful and friendly, and our family of five was welcomed and treated very kindly. The food was classic po boys, steamed shrimp, as well as hamburgers and salads.  There is ample parking in the rear of the building, and it's very close to Jellystone Park (where we were staying). They don't serve alcohol.
We would eat here again!
Friendly staff and excellent food! We stayed in Luray for a week and ended to eating here twice because it was so good the first time. Fried green tomatoes and crab fluff were excellent!
What a great little place! We were just driving by and decided to stop in and give it a try. Staff was friendly, service was fast and food well worth it!

Food wasn‚Äôt that great @ all! I get better seafood from the yellow Gordon‚Äôs fisherman bag from the frozen food section! Took forever to get food & drink refills... so small inside I‚Äôm glad I didn‚Äôt take my kids.

First glance it reminds me of a little crab shack. It's definitely a tiny place had some cute fishing decor, and a "holiday tree".

The food was a no. The clams were dry, fries were soggy, the fried shrimp was actually good/average, and the mac and cheese well..... Let's just say it's like little shells covered in velveta baked in a dish and then just microwaved when needed. If I wanted leftovers I wouldn't have stayed home and looked in my fridge.

I waited forever to even be offered a refill, and once again I only had water (seems to be a thing in the Luray area). The specials aren't special or a money savor.

The dessert was probably the best part and we ended up getting it to go because I couldn't take the waitress anymore. It was a lemon raspberry cheesecake. And it had like a cake/fluff layer on it and a whipped top.

After all this though I don't really suggest it. What is great to locals is sometimes just average to travelers.
My family and I love eating here. Great food. Great service.
Great fried clams and fish & chips. Beer batter that actually had a beer flavor! I will definitely go again.
Really good prices for some pretty good food. Not masterpieces but very much worth the price and a very relaxed atmosphere.
This place is AMAZING! Go try the crab balls...or anything really. Everything I've ever had here is just wonderful!
Ok, you're in Luray, VA.  The whole town eats here. If they'll go light on the batter, all of the seafood is just fine. And the people are a delight!
great food & great service! if you can get there when the catfish is on the menu then GO! we loved it along with their cole slaw it's delicious
The food is always delicious, fresh, and inexpensive. They offer a large variety of foods! Servers are always friendly!

They have excellent customer service and  he best seafood in town..not to mention great prices also. The atmosphere can't be beat..this is an experience you won't want to miss out on. Plus the owner is a musician who opened up for some of the biggest name bands .now playing locally. You will enjpy.
Good food, friendly little place & the best part was the recommendation for entertainment that night the owner gave us. Made it an awesome night!
Love the food, always delicious.. They staff is very welcoming and friendly.
Good food and atmosphere. People were friendly. Wide assortment of options. Service was good.
Great service. Food was excellent. Loved it!
Food is cheap, but always good. One of my favorite local restaurants.
Great food, very friendly owners and staff!
Waitresses are very friendly and they make an effort to please the customers. The food not only is comforting, but the food tastes amazing.
The food is ok, it just doesn't have that pop. But still the customer service good, they nice and friendly. I would go back.
Great Seafood and the people are nice! I'm from Maryland lol
THEIR FOOD IS GREAT AND THE SERVICE IS EXCELLENT !!!
Always a great place to eat and great atmosphere foods good owner comes out when he can to greet and talk to customers
Amazing place for quick, friendly service and delicious foods. Especially the steamed fish
Food is great!Friendly staff,reasonable prices.
Absolutely love the staff the owners and the food is fantastic!!!!
Good service, great food.
Great staff serving great food.
Great food. Love the bbq sandwich with slaw.

Great food as always!!

Went for lunch so YMMV. Promptly seated upon entry, friendly and attentive service. Pizza was good, I got the Maldini special. Coworkers got a veggie pizza and pasta and they seemed to like it as well. Overall it was a good experience.

Okay. This place is a an aggressively red-sauce Italian restaurant. But that is the charm of it. The menu is just massive and kind of all over the place. However there are some real jems on it. I especially recommend the subs.

We've ordered a few pizzas and other food from Maldini's, and it's always good. Also, shout out to our delivery person. He is SO nice! Every time he's delivered, he expresses thanks for supporting their business. I'm sorry I couldn't hear your very well tonight over our dogs barking. :)

Do yourself a favor and order food from them. Yum!
They are the warmest most friendly people I have met in a long time. Their food and atmosphere are like heaven. If you are looking for authentic Italian food this is the place to go

The prosciutto in the appetizer was some of the best I every had, but I wasn‚Äôt a fan of the sauce on the pizza.  The table was also in need of a wipe down. Really can't go wrong with a pizza from Maldini's!! Their crust has an excellent crisp to it, and the sauce is quite flavorful. 10/10 would recommend to anyone!

The food and service was absolutely amazing!  I ordered the calamari for an appetizer, and it's honestly the best calamari I've ever had.  The seasoning used on it was the best I ever had. My food was very delicious. I had the personal pan pizza with sausage topping. For dessert, cannoli with a couple cups of coffee. My whole order, with tip was about $18.60.  I thought the price was very reasonable. My waitress was very friendly and helpful. And the restaurant was clean and it had a steady flow of customers.

My only complaints were they seemed short staffed. My waitress was the only staff member I could see helping customers, and no rest rooms available, at least that is what it said on the entrance doors.

With that said, I still return to this restaurant and try their other dishes.

Love Italian food. I would take a date here. Great atmosphere. But I work with high risk patients. If the guys in the kitchen wore masks and gloves while preparing food, it would be cool. Its hard to find a restaurant that takes proper Covid precautions. Just a thought. Think about those that work with high risk populations. We are on the front lines every day. Its also hard being single and dating in a pandemic. Stay safe, everyone!
Wonderful food.  Plentiful portions.  Great wine.  Good, friendly service.

The pizza was terrible, so i was hoping to try something new from them tonight. instead, i find that not a single employee was following covid guidelines when i walked in. two put on masks when i made eye contact. a third put his unmasked, un-netted (he had hair and a beard that require it) head through the kitchen window to talk to the (unmasked) cooks. i literally saw spittle come out of his mouth. and they have signs posted that masks are required, and even sell masks (for $15!!!). if they cant be bothered to take two seconds to put on a mask, are they really taking the time to properly wash their hands?

I am literally mad at myself for not eating at Maldini's before this year. How does Maldini have the very best chicken tenders and onion rings I've ever eaten?! Everything we've gotten from fried food to their traditional Italian entrees are absolutely delicious. But honestly, their customer service is the absolute best. Everyone we have encountered there is so friendly and nice. It doesn't feel fake in the slightest. I've only been here 4 times but I've always been impressed.
Family owned, food is always consistent and fresh. Pizza is amazing! We have been going there for almost 9 years.

This is one of my family's favorite restaurants. The employees are so kind. They are always giving my kids little gifts. We do not drive in my husband Rides the bus. In inclement weather he always invites them to stand inside getting a soda waiting for the bus. It's the small things that count that make you value an establishment.

I have been going to this place since I moved to the neighborhood. I have had pretty descent food and service, however I was a little bit sad that I ordered a pizza and a salad and it was delivered where the toppings were on only half the pizza and the Mediterranean salad didn't have any feta or pepperchini peppers.  I tried contacting Maldini's via email and I have heard no response back. I will go back to support our local business, but I would at least like to have a response back. UPDATE, Never heard back from the restaurant about this issue and it has been about 2 months.

We ordered two brick oven pizzas and the portobello appetizer and everything was cooked to perfection and the flavors were so authentic! Loved every bite and we are planning to return to try other dishes, such as pasta or sandwiches!
Great Italian at reasonable prices. Hard to get a good meal to go during this pandemic. Thanks guys for your great service.
Excellent food. Great service. True Italian cuisine! Very friendly and loving staff. Family oriented restaurant.
The place is nice and clean. Staff was very nice. I tried the Manicotti and was not impressed.

Excellent! Loved this place. I went in here after work not realizing how classy this place is however despite looking pretty rough they still treated me with the best service and respect. I was seated by a very professional young man of about 10 years old wearing a tux. Very cool. And the food is top notch!  I highly recommend this place. Great place to take a date as well.

Not the worst Italian I've had from the area, but far from the best. The pasta I ordered had little sauce. To put that into perspective, I'll elaborate. If I had asked for lite sauce, I still would have expected more sauce than
I got.

The sausage and pepperoni in my dish were flavorful and delicious. The bread that came with the meal was just ok. The sauce was good too, but there was nowhere near enough of it.

I would have given 4 stars, but my wife said that her pasta was bland, and she had to add her own seasonings to it.

I'd probably be willing to give this place another chance in the future.

Nice service here. The food is very heavy and they do odd things like serve tortilla chips with marinara sauce. The do have a nice beer selection and great happy hour specials starting at 2. This would probably be a great place to watch a game but I'm not sure I would come here for the food.
So glad they are open.  Always great food.

Very slow service. They need to hire help. There was one person serving behind the counter and serving tables. It may have been just today, but it shouldn't have to take this long to eat. Food is good.

The food was tasty and the service was great. I also love their program they have for those in need. I'd suggest everyone look them up and help them out with their plan to help the community by providing meals to those in need.
Awesome place and great staff

My household regularly orders take out and delivery from here. My one roommate loves their Philly sandwhich. Last time we went at 930 at night to get take out and they were really helpful and friendly. Even though they were abouy to close. I got the Mediterranean panini and it was delicious

Service was great, food was great. Even after eating we got another pizza, with smiles on their faces they served us and didn't have any grudges. Great experience

Sadly inconsistent. Right around the corner, used to go there all the time, but now the food is spotty. Some days great, some days ok, and occasionally bad.

It took us more than an hour to receive our lunch of a pizza, a sandwich and an order of lasagna. Oh, and there was only one other table occupied on a Saturday. If you have all day to wait for a meal, this is the place to go!
Best an biggest stromboli I've ever seen an ate
Good Italian so long as you don't order anything too adventurous, stick to the traditional offerings and you will be well served (pun intended).

Maldini's ristorante is my favorite, with the family, on a date, or just alone to get your thoughts together. The atmosphere is the right temperature to enhance your feelings. The food and service is tailored to your needs delightfully.   The Goodfellas of Italy
I keep trying to give this place a chance. I'd honestly recommend not leaving the tails on shrimp for the pastas. The cook seems like he's bored.

I had a most delicious meal. Everything I had there was excellent, starting with the Mediterranean salad, moving on to some of the best bruschetta I have eaten, and my pasta dish made with there spinach pasta stuffed with artichokes in a mushroom white sauce. This is the second time I have eaten there and the quality of the food continues to be excellent.

Best Italian delivery in the ForestHill area. Haven't tried much else except the pizza but the pizza is good enough. Can't complain.

Great food and service! Also has a long bar and best happy hour in town.
The food is absolutely fantastic and the pizza is as close to a NY slice as you can get in  Richmond VA.!

The food was very good. We had a large party and were served well. The waiters were nice and it was overall a good experience.
Great place for good pizza!
I thought good was excellent. Generous portions for left overs. I had the rib eye, very good. Wife's Carbonara was superb. Will go there again.
Its ok pretty greesy but taste good.

My family enjoyed the well drinks and wine for $5 and said that they definitely got their money worth. We will definitely be visiting again.

So I was in the restaurant business, so I COMPLETELY understand that things happen and it's not always under your control. So I called to try to see if I could figure out what I could do because things were wrong and it was not enjoyable at all. When I called and asked to speak to a manager, an obviously angry person named Mike answered the phone with an indistinguishable statement; I guess the name of the restaurant no hello, no name, no nothing. I asked can I speak to a manager, please and got a "she's not here." answer.  So I asked "Ok who do I talk to about a messed up order I just received. He said, "Oh, Did you order it through Grub Hub?" I was like yes then he said, "well I got to go to the computer, hold on." very matter factly. So I was like ok?? Then when he came back, he started reading off the order to me, and I confirmed that was my order. I'm giving this place 4 üåüüåü üåüüåü mainly because we were totally surprised, in a really good way. We'd been here several years ago and it was just meh...nothing special. We drove by last year and it looked closed down. Being on the Northern Neck, there's only a hand full of decent restaurants. We thought we'd give Leadbelly's at the Fairport Marina another look-see because we heard it WAS open.  Glad we did!

Nothing fancy. Nothing. It's a Marina. You can smell the sea lingering from the work boats docked there. There's outdoor screened porch seating, but it was closed "due to extreme heat". The waitresses wear t-shirts advertising the restaurant...and they wear flip-flops...probably against code, but what the heck.

There were 4 of us. I ordered the fried oyster appetizer ($12) with a side of fried cabbage ($2.25) My dinner mates each ordered the oyster platter for $20 which came with 2 sides and "big butt rolls".

Now...we've been going to another place where the oysters are tasty, but the portions have shrunk over time. When our friendly waitress (who grew up on the water and didn't eat seafood) brought our meals, I was pleasantly surprised at the huge mound of oysters. They had just the right amount of breading and the fried cabbage was delicious, cooked just right.  I forgot to count how many oysters I had,  but I know this: I got a big mess (a whole lot) of plump fried oysters for not a lot of money. My buddies had more on their plates than I had for the appetizer portion and they couldn't finish...they toted the remains home.

If you are in the area of Fairport on the Northern Neck of Virgina, definitely give this place a try. Down home, local hangout is worth  the trip!

I lived in Pulaski many years. This chinese place actually is not bad. I am surprised they have so many negative reviews. I used to take my mom and cousins here when my mom and I visited Pulaski to see some of our family. They really aren't that bad. The food is always good and quite tasty.

There is a problem I saw on my last visit here though. Just as another reviewer said, they will put customers on speaker phone. You can hear all the customer's credit card information and everything. That is very dangerous and they need to watch out doing this. Never have I seen this anywhere but here. I told them they should never do that again. Hopefully they won't.
